Nice place, terrible opening band.  Service was prompt and friendly, food was decent (margherita pizza had a lovely crispy crust but was a bit too salty).  Halloween decorations were creative and fun, almost everyone was in costume, which was super fun. However, a very disappointing opening band - Ledbetter and His Best Bets.  They bragged about not having rehearsed, which felt like a slap in the face after we paid a cover for the live music. And their lack of effort really showed in their performance.  The band used the same arrangement and rhythm for every song - i.e., all six musicians played together at medium-high volume throughout every song, creating a monotonous similarity.  Only one person sang, which added to the monotony, and he forgot the words several times, even on songs he himself wrote.  Their cover of Joe Cockers Feelin All Right was competent, but all the other covers sounded the same, and the original songs were uninspiring.  We had to leave before the second band played so no comment on them.
Its not my favorite place, but they have trivia on Tuesdays!

It is a Spa with cabins that is located a little more than 20 miles from the entrance to Yosemite Park, close to all the lakes in the Mammoth region. The spa is very good, however the mattresses on the beds in the cabin we had, 109, are expired making the night uncomfortable. In addition, the restaurant inside the Spa closes at 9 pm, limiting the possibility of eating when it gets late on the days walks. If you visit in summer, with nightfall starting at 8 pm, it becomes difficult to get to eat after spending all day in the park. The good thing is that since it has a kitchen, if you expect to leave the park late, you can cook in the cabin. The recommendation is to be attentive with the food.
